field.value:
This is useful for inheriting a controller's behaviour, and keeping it's views, instead of having to override manually in subclass code. i.e.:

//different layout
[Layout("FooSub")]
[ControllerDetails(UseViewFor=typeof(Foo))]
class FooSub: Foo
{
}

Instead of 
[Layout...]
class FooSub:Foo
{
public void Index()
{
  base();
  RenderView("foo","index");
}
}


Basically for utilising controller functionality in different parts of a website (i.e. in an iframe window, which may have a different layout, but same views).

This hits the Controller class & may introduce some subtle bugs. 

It has also only been tested with nvelocity, but others should work.
